00:23.254 --> 00:26.007
Hello. I'm Linda Lee Cadwell.

00:26.094 --> 00:28.927
I welcome you to this
special laserdisc edition...

00:29.014 --> 00:32.323
of Dragon: The Bruce Lee Story.

00:32.414 --> 00:36.566
The film you're about to see
is the story of a real human being:

00:36.654 --> 00:39.248
a struggling person,
a loving person...

00:39.334 --> 00:42.963
with a great many levels
to his character.

00:43.054 --> 00:47.684
When I first spoke to Rob Cohen,
the director and cowriter of Dragon...

00:47.774 --> 00:51.210
about making a motion picture
of my husband's life...

00:51.294 --> 00:55.572
I told him that I wanted people
to know about Bruce Lee the man.

00:55.654 --> 00:58.088
Not just the powerful
martial artist...

00:58.174 --> 01:00.847
but also the loving
husband and father...

01:00.934 --> 01:04.449
the philosopher and the teacher.

01:04.534 --> 01:07.844
Rob's creation
is the story of that man.

01:07.934 --> 01:12.450
Even before Bruce Lee was a role model
to millions of young people...

01:12.534 --> 01:15.412
he was a role model
to his own children.

01:15.494 --> 01:19.726
Before he was a heroic image
to people all over the world...

01:19.814 --> 01:22.965
he was a hero in our own lives.

01:23.054 --> 01:25.966
Dragon will give you insight
into Bruce Lee...

01:26.054 --> 01:29.126
the man who became a hero.

01:29.214 --> 01:33.765
As you'll see from watching Dragon,
Bruce had a tremendous energy.

01:33.854 --> 01:37.563
ln fact, as a child
he was called Mao Tse-tung...

01:37.654 --> 01:40.566
Chinese for " never sits still."

01:40.654 --> 01:45.091
This energy fired the creative essence
of his entire being.

01:45.174 --> 01:49.087
He had the remarkable capability
of channeling this energy...

01:49.174 --> 01:52.962
focusing it, disciplining it
to serve his goals.

01:53.054 --> 01:55.204
This high-intensity energy...

01:55.294 --> 01:58.764
is also the essence of this film.

01:58.854 --> 02:01.129
Bruce could be funny
and lighthearted.

02:01.214 --> 02:05.446
l've never laughed so much in my life
as I did when I was with him.

02:05.534 --> 02:08.048
And he could be tender and kind.

02:08.133 --> 02:12.366
He had so much to give in his life,
and he gave it all.

02:12.454 --> 02:15.924
A life need not be measured
in numbers of years...

02:16.014 --> 02:19.211
but by the contributions
of the individual.

02:19.294 --> 02:22.650
By this measure,
Bruce was a sage.

02:22.734 --> 02:25.043
Saint Augustine once said...

02:25.134 --> 02:27.204
"The key to immortality...

02:27.294 --> 02:31.412
is first living a life
worth remembering."

02:31.494 --> 02:34.884
There was also a much deeper side
to Bruce's personality...

02:34.974 --> 02:37.568
that Dragon tells
especially well...

02:37.654 --> 02:40.805
and that is
his philosophical side.

02:40.894 --> 02:44.284
lmmersed in the Eastern
and Western philosophies...

02:44.374 --> 02:47.525
Bruce was a great
and deep thinker...

02:47.614 --> 02:52.210
always contemplating life
and the meaning of his own existence.

02:52.294 --> 02:54.410
Through study and intuition...

02:54.494 --> 02:57.964
he had an inner awareness
of his own potential...

02:58.054 --> 03:01.490
and he strove constantly
to fulfill it.

03:01.574 --> 03:05.169
He was a student,
a teacher and an artist.

03:05.254 --> 03:09.725
To him, the discipline of martial arts
was not just a means to fight better...

03:09.814 --> 03:12.089
it was a way to live better...

03:12.174 --> 03:15.769
through the perfection
of his mind and body.

03:15.854 --> 03:19.608
By increasing his powers of awareness
through self-knowledge...

03:19.694 --> 03:23.448
Bruce was constantly fine-tuning
his inner perceptions...

03:23.534 --> 03:27.686
and their relationship
to things going on around him.

03:27.774 --> 03:30.413
Through his own process
of self-evaluation...

03:30.494 --> 03:33.247
he evolved his own martial arts...

03:33.334 --> 03:36.531
which he called " jeet kune do."

03:36.614 --> 03:38.570
When he was offered
the chance to make films...

03:38.654 --> 03:42.727
Bruce saw an opportunity
to show his beloved Chinese culture...

03:42.814 --> 03:45.248
and his special art to millions.

03:45.334 --> 03:49.452
And as usual, he focused
all of his energy on it.

03:49.534 --> 03:52.207
Here was a chance
to communicate to people...

03:52.294 --> 03:54.967
how he felt about
the martial arts...

03:55.054 --> 03:57.773
and to show
his way of living it...

03:57.854 --> 04:02.928
and to show the world the unique
power and beauty of Asian culture.

04:03.014 --> 04:06.404
The world of the motion picture
became the best classroom...

04:06.494 --> 04:11.045
for the teachings of
the Little Dragon, La Siu Lom.

04:11.134 --> 04:13.807
With his new ambition, though,
came new boundaries...

04:13.894 --> 04:17.045
mostly in the negative ways
that Asians were depicted...

04:17.134 --> 04:19.523
in film and television.

04:19.613 --> 04:22.890
Bruce wasn't a person
who recognized barriers of any sort...

04:22.974 --> 04:25.647
either in filmmaking
or martial arts.

04:25.734 --> 04:30.012
He wouldn't be a party
to the stereotypes of the time.

04:30.094 --> 04:33.404
ln tearing down the barriers
of fear and prejudice...

04:33.494 --> 04:37.043
that were so firmly entrenched
in Western filmmaking...

04:37.134 --> 04:39.887
Bruce opened the door
for people of all races...

04:39.974 --> 04:45.173
cultures and disabilities
to fulfill their potentials.

04:45.254 --> 04:48.451
Bruce's work crossed the boundaries
of film and martial arts...

04:48.534 --> 04:54.291
and showed people in all walks of life
that they could realize their dreams.

04:54.374 --> 04:57.571
lf somebody told Bruce
he couldn't do something...

04:57.654 --> 05:01.772
he would not accept it
without exploring and examining it.

05:01.854 --> 05:04.732
While he had great respect
for tradition...

05:04.814 --> 05:08.443
he was not a slave to it,
and if he saw a better way...

05:08.534 --> 05:12.368
he was faithful to
the integrity of his opinions.

05:12.454 --> 05:16.686
He ruffled some feathers, but he
also changed a lot of attitudes...

05:16.774 --> 05:19.811
and he definitely
changed the way martial arts...

05:19.894 --> 05:22.772
and Asian culture are perceived.

05:22.854 --> 05:25.926
Now 20 years after he left us...

05:26.014 --> 05:28.926
he's still changing people's attitudes.

05:29.014 --> 05:31.733
This is what
the film Dragon does so well.

05:31.814 --> 05:35.124
lt does not show
Bruce Lee, a Chinese man...

05:35.214 --> 05:37.774
or Bruce Lee, a fighting man...

05:37.854 --> 05:40.527
or Bruce Lee, a family man.

05:40.614 --> 05:43.174
lt is all of these
and none of these.

05:43.254 --> 05:48.453
Dragon is about Bruce Lee,
a real human being.

05:48.534 --> 05:52.049
I'm often asked to speculate
on what Bruce would be doing now...

05:52.134 --> 05:54.045
if he were still here.

05:54.134 --> 05:58.093
I think it's safe to say that
he would still be involved in film.

05:58.174 --> 06:00.529
He loved film,
and it was his passion...

06:00.614 --> 06:03.287
to share his philosophy
with the whole world...

06:03.374 --> 06:07.925
through a medium that could
entertain as well as inform.

06:08.014 --> 06:12.212
He would probably have continued
to write and produce his own pictures...

06:12.294 --> 06:14.967
and to create opportunities
for others...

06:15.054 --> 06:18.285
to create their own
special kind of art.

06:18.374 --> 06:22.162
And Bruce, I am sure,
would have loved Dragon.

06:22.254 --> 06:25.132
Rob Cohen has done
justice to the man.

06:25.214 --> 06:27.284
And as for Jason Scott Lee...

06:27.374 --> 06:30.525
I almost feel that it was worth
waiting for all this time...

06:30.614 --> 06:34.846
for Jason to grow up
and be old enough to play Bruce.

06:34.934 --> 06:39.166
I sincerely hope you enjoy
Dragon: The Bruce Lee Story.

06:39.254 --> 06:42.246
Watch it with the knowledge
that you are indeed witnessing...

06:42.334 --> 06:45.007
the true humor, wisdom...

06:45.094 --> 06:49.007
and yes,
the power of the man I knew.

12:43.648 --> 12:46.446
Kung fu is more than
a system of fighting.

12:46.488 --> 12:48.558
lt's a system of thought.

12:48.648 --> 12:52.800
You must outthink your opponent,
whatever form he takes...

12:52.848 --> 12:56.807
because some of them
will be more than just men.

12:56.848 --> 12:59.567
What else could it be, sifu?

12:59.648 --> 13:02.606
We all have inner demons
to fight.

13:02.688 --> 13:07.079
We call these demons fear
and hatred and anger.

13:07.128 --> 13:10.598
lf you don't conquer them,
then a life of a hundred years...

13:10.648 --> 13:12.525
is a tragedy.

13:12.568 --> 13:14.843
lf you do,
a life of a single day...

13:14.888 --> 13:17.482
can be a triumph.

13:58.408 --> 14:01.241
Don't worry about it.
Don't worry.

14:02.528 --> 14:04.598
Excuse me, my son.

14:06.168 --> 14:07.999
Uh, six pints
of beer, mate.

14:08.088 --> 14:10.602
- No.
- Aw, come on.

14:13.568 --> 14:16.036
Oh, God, what about
that one there?

14:30.608 --> 14:33.406
Hello. Mind if I take over?
Go on, piss off!

14:34.528 --> 14:37.326
Big boy!

14:39.528 --> 14:41.519
Hey, look,
I'm Fred Astaire!

14:51.288 --> 14:53.438
She's a bit frisky, isn't she?

14:53.528 --> 14:58.204
Oh, yeah. Come on, one, two.
Oh, I love it when they fight back.

14:58.248 --> 15:00.284
One, two, come on!

15:00.328 --> 15:03.525
Stay back. Stay back.
Back in-- Hey, hey! Back in line.

15:08.968 --> 15:11.766
- What do you want?
- I want to dance with her.

15:11.848 --> 15:14.646
This one's mine.
Get one of your own.

15:16.648 --> 15:19.162
She is one of my own.

15:40.408 --> 15:42.717
Hold it, lads.

15:42.768 --> 15:46.522
Leave him to me.
Come on, try that again.

15:46.568 --> 15:50.004
I'm gonna get you,
you little yellow bastard.

15:50.088 --> 15:52.648
Smash your face in.

15:52.728 --> 15:54.559
Try it again, huh?

16:40.488 --> 16:41.477
Hey, Bob!

16:49.368 --> 16:51.199
Wanna try this?

16:55.448 --> 16:58.406
Okay.

18:04.168 --> 18:06.238
Papa!

18:06.328 --> 18:09.479
The police were here.
They're looking for you.

18:09.568 --> 18:12.480
- I know.
- The sailor's in hospital
with a punctured lung.

18:12.568 --> 18:15.605
- He might die.
- He was making trouble.
He started it.

18:15.688 --> 18:19.476
He's the nephew of the Assistant
Police lnspector of Kowloon.

18:19.528 --> 18:21.996
I can hide out
with my friends.

18:22.088 --> 18:24.966
You don't have
any friends now!

18:37.888 --> 18:40.482
The cops will be back.

18:40.528 --> 18:43.042
I should
get out of here.

18:43.088 --> 18:44.965
Sit down.

18:50.288 --> 18:52.563
l've thought a lot
about this...

18:52.648 --> 18:55.685
for a very long time.

18:55.768 --> 18:58.965
- You'll have to leave Hong Kong.
- For how long?

18:59.048 --> 19:00.879
Forever.

19:02.488 --> 19:05.446
This is a joke, right?
You're joking.

19:05.528 --> 19:09.919
Listen to me, Sai-Fong, you'll die
in Hong Kong. l've seen it.

19:10.008 --> 19:12.966
You're too superstitious,
Papa.

19:18.008 --> 19:19.999
You're a man now.
Almost.

19:20.088 --> 19:23.364
You have a right to know everything.
You had an older brother.

19:23.408 --> 19:26.559
He died in childbirth.

19:26.608 --> 19:28.838
The demon took him
away from us.

19:28.928 --> 19:32.000
The firstborn man-child
is very valuable.

19:32.088 --> 19:35.922
So when you were born,
I name you Sai-Fong, a girl's name.

19:36.008 --> 19:40.399
We dress you in dresses so the demon
wouldn't know I had another son.

19:40.488 --> 19:44.003
I made you speak English,
all so we could fool him.

19:44.088 --> 19:45.919
But now he knows.

19:47.248 --> 19:49.125
And he's coming for you.

19:50.568 --> 19:53.036
You must leave tonight.

19:53.128 --> 19:55.164
Where, Papa?
Where can I go?

19:55.208 --> 19:58.359
You love American movies.

19:58.408 --> 20:00.968
You love American cars.

20:01.008 --> 20:04.159
- You go to America.
- America?

20:04.248 --> 20:07.843
I was in America on tour
with the Canton Opera Company in 1940.

20:07.888 --> 20:11.005
San Francisco.
Doing The Drunken Princess.

20:11.048 --> 20:13.403
November 27th,
you were born.

20:13.448 --> 20:16.758
That morning I got you
and three good reviews.

20:16.808 --> 20:19.686
I was very proud.
Come here. Come here.

20:25.168 --> 20:27.045
This...

20:27.088 --> 20:29.079
is your birth
certificate.

20:29.128 --> 20:31.358
"Bruce Lee."

20:31.448 --> 20:34.804
- lt sounded very American.
- lt sure does.

20:38.408 --> 20:41.445
You were born there.
Show this to the immigration man.

20:41.528 --> 20:44.645
They have to let you in.

20:44.688 --> 20:46.565
You need money
to go to America.

20:51.848 --> 20:53.725
lt's yours.

20:54.768 --> 20:57.123
I saved it for you...

20:57.168 --> 20:59.045
for a day like today.

21:02.848 --> 21:04.884
I don't know
what to say.

21:08.888 --> 21:10.879
Say you'll do better.

21:10.968 --> 21:13.357
Tell me you'll make
a big noise in America...

21:13.448 --> 21:16.246
so I can hear it
over here.

21:42.728 --> 21:45.959
No.

21:46.048 --> 21:47.879
- Do you speak English?
- Yeah.

21:47.968 --> 21:51.438
I'm practicing my English.
Going to America.

21:51.528 --> 21:53.996
l've always wanted
to go to America.

21:55.608 --> 21:58.361
James Dean.

21:58.408 --> 22:01.559
French Fries. The sky's the limit,
that's what they say.

22:01.608 --> 22:05.044
Not a Chinaman's chance.
They say that too.

22:05.128 --> 22:07.961
- You ever hear that?
- No.

22:08.008 --> 22:11.887
You know, the Chinese,
we built the railroads there.

22:11.968 --> 22:14.402
The Americans, the gwailo,
would lower Chinamens...

22:14.488 --> 22:17.525
over the cliff in baskets
to set the dynamite.

22:17.608 --> 22:21.123
Get pulled up too slow,
bang!

22:21.208 --> 22:23.164
Rope break.

22:23.208 --> 22:25.597
Bye-bye. Bye-bye.

22:25.688 --> 22:27.679
Bye-bye.

22:27.768 --> 22:32.125
Americans say,
"Not a Chinaman's chance" ...

22:32.168 --> 22:34.728
and round-eyed gwailo
would laugh.

22:36.368 --> 22:38.245
We're not human to them.

22:39.688 --> 22:42.248
- How do you know?
- I'm a history teacher.

22:44.728 --> 22:46.878
Things are different now.
lt's today.

22:46.968 --> 22:50.881
- Sure, sure. Maybe.
- I'm different.

22:50.928 --> 22:53.283
Sure. Sure.

22:53.328 --> 22:56.240
I am. You'll see.

23:13.408 --> 23:17.287
Order, please. One pork lo mein,
one kung pao chicken.

23:17.368 --> 23:20.007
Hey. Hey.

23:20.048 --> 23:21.959
Hi.

23:22.048 --> 23:24.004
My name is April.

23:24.048 --> 23:26.437
- Bruce.
- I know.

23:29.848 --> 23:32.442
Hey, Lee! Clean up!

23:34.888 --> 23:37.527
Hey, Lee! Clean up!

23:41.448 --> 23:44.758
- Lee, clean it up.
- Yes, Miss Yang.

23:44.808 --> 23:49.006
Mr. Ho, you're here to cook,
not to make trouble.

24:32.128 --> 24:35.279
Go! Fight!

24:35.368 --> 24:38.166
Win!
Go, fight, win!

24:38.248 --> 24:40.716
Hit it! Whoo!

24:40.808 --> 24:43.606
Michael! Come on! Yeah!

24:45.288 --> 24:47.119
You know what Margaret Mead--

24:47.208 --> 24:51.520
Go! Fight! Win!

24:51.568 --> 24:53.445
Go, fight, win!
Hit it!

25:16.328 --> 25:19.126
"'And I have made
a mistake,' Robert Jor--

25:19.208 --> 25:22.837
Robert Jor-- Jordan
thought to himself.

25:22.888 --> 25:25.356
'I have told
the Spaniards...

25:25.448 --> 25:27.837
we could do
something better...'"

25:27.928 --> 25:30.726
Better-err. Better.

25:30.768 --> 25:33.123
"'Than they can.'"

25:58.368 --> 26:02.122
One order peking duck.

26:02.208 --> 26:04.039
Ah.

26:09.608 --> 26:12.247
You son of a bitch!

26:12.328 --> 26:14.364
You grab my girl!

26:25.128 --> 26:27.198
Give me a knife! Aah!

27:52.008 --> 27:54.886
Get the son of a bitch!
Kill him! Kill him!

29:41.608 --> 29:43.997
Get back inside, all of you!

29:44.048 --> 29:45.925
Come on! Come on!

30:02.968 --> 30:05.118
Sit down.

30:16.808 --> 30:18.639
Two weeks pay.

30:20.888 --> 30:23.197
Two weeks severance.

30:28.808 --> 30:32.437
- What's this?
- All-purpose loan.

30:32.488 --> 30:35.321
You got a lot of money, Lee.
What you gonna do?

30:35.368 --> 30:37.279
- I guess l'd better--
- I tell you what to do.

30:37.328 --> 30:40.843
Take April on the town.

30:40.928 --> 30:44.159
Buy her nice clothes.
Check into big hotel.

30:44.208 --> 30:46.722
Have lots of sex.

30:46.768 --> 30:48.963
Have food brought up
to you in bed.

30:49.048 --> 30:50.879
Drink champagne
and whiskey.

30:50.968 --> 30:53.687
Now money all gone.

30:55.208 --> 30:58.245
April be gone, too,
like money.

30:58.288 --> 31:00.165
You come back to me.

31:00.208 --> 31:02.642
I put you in kitchen,
wash dishes to pay back loan.

31:02.728 --> 31:05.765
By that time you're no longer young,
you're no longer handsome.

31:05.808 --> 31:08.686
You're nothing
but a... dishwasher.

31:10.168 --> 31:13.205
That one choice.
There are others.

31:13.288 --> 31:15.119
Like what?

31:15.208 --> 31:18.166
They say education
is good. Hmm.

31:18.248 --> 31:21.877
l've heard that.
Me, personally...

31:21.928 --> 31:24.283
I hope you go
with April.

31:24.328 --> 31:26.796
I can always use
a good...

31:26.888 --> 31:29.925
dishwasher!

32:06.008 --> 32:09.125
- Time's up. Come on, man.
- I'm not... finished yet.

32:09.168 --> 32:11.079
Yeah, you are.
We work out at 3:00.

32:11.168 --> 32:13.602
See that clock?
lt's 3:00. Come on.

32:13.688 --> 32:16.964
- Where does it say that
in the rule book?
- Ooh. The rule book.

32:17.048 --> 32:20.802
You been readin' the wrong rule books.
Read the ones in English.

32:22.728 --> 32:25.288
- What's that mean?
- See? That's what I mean.

32:25.368 --> 32:27.199
Your kind
don't understand English.

32:27.288 --> 32:29.279
- My kind?
- Yeah.

32:29.368 --> 32:31.757
Gooks, chinks. You guys
killed my dad in Korea.

32:31.848 --> 32:34.999
- You think I'm happy
to see you in my gym?
- Don't touch me.

32:37.928 --> 32:41.841
- Or what? Huh?
- Or l'll touch you back.

32:44.168 --> 32:47.046
Come on, touch me, dink.
Come on.

32:47.088 --> 32:50.239
- Come on, touch me, chink. Come on.
- Hit him, Joe.

32:50.328 --> 32:53.604
Quit looking at him
and touch me, chink.

32:53.648 --> 32:56.321
Come on, man.

32:56.368 --> 32:59.280
He's scared of you, man.

32:59.368 --> 33:02.405
He's scared.

33:02.448 --> 33:05.360
- Mr. Henderson, we so sorry.
- Are you coming?

33:05.448 --> 33:08.326
I have to finish
my workout.

33:08.368 --> 33:10.757
Might as well finish
on you.

33:14.088 --> 33:17.524
- Finish him, Joe.
- Okay, chink, let's go.

33:19.368 --> 33:21.199
Ken, Andy,
get off the mat!

33:21.288 --> 33:24.598
- Go on, man,
I'm gonna kill this guy.
- You can take him, Joe.

33:24.648 --> 33:26.525
Wait.

33:26.568 --> 33:29.878
What is this? What are you gonna do,
stink me to death?

33:29.928 --> 33:31.805
Come on! Come on.

33:31.848 --> 33:34.681
Wait. Wait.
So sorry.

33:36.248 --> 33:39.604
Oh! What is this,
a fight or a striptease?

33:39.688 --> 33:42.998
Come on! Come on!

33:43.048 --> 33:44.766
- Okay, I ready.
- Yeah?

33:48.368 --> 33:50.723
Aah! Very good
shadow boxing!

33:50.808 --> 33:52.878
You... Aaaah!

33:54.648 --> 33:57.242
- Chinks can jump real high, huh?
- Come on, Joe!

33:57.288 --> 33:59.961
Come on.

34:00.008 --> 34:03.239
Come on, show him what for, Joe.

34:03.328 --> 34:05.159
Aaah!

34:05.248 --> 34:07.603
