There are some papers
to sign, Mrs. Lee.

01:03:56.208 --> 01:03:59.837
- Mrs. Lee.
- Huh?

01:03:59.928 --> 01:04:02.726
Some-- There are some papers.
Some papers.

01:04:26.168 --> 01:04:31.845
You know, this thing's kinda sexy. Maybe
we can keep it after you're better.

01:04:31.888 --> 01:04:34.607
I'm sorry.

01:04:34.688 --> 01:04:37.441
lt was a bad joke.

01:04:40.808 --> 01:04:45.040
I know you're mad. Don't be mad.
lt'll only make things worse.

01:04:45.128 --> 01:04:49.280
Worse? Couldn't take a hell of a lot
to make things worse.

01:04:49.328 --> 01:04:52.764
- You should've told me
where you were going.
- Why?

01:04:52.808 --> 01:04:55.800
Because I'm your wife, that's why!
I had a right to know.

01:04:55.848 --> 01:05:00.046
You might wanna think about that.
The wife part, I mean.

01:05:03.928 --> 01:05:08.001
- What're you saying?
- Take a good look at me, Linda.

01:05:13.088 --> 01:05:15.966
- So we've got a little trouble.
- This is more than a little trouble!

01:05:16.008 --> 01:05:18.203
Okay, so we've got
big trouble!

01:05:18.248 --> 01:05:21.046
You're always going on about
the beauties of your Chinese culture!

01:05:21.128 --> 01:05:24.484
Let me tell you about the beauties
of my culture! We love big trouble!

01:05:24.568 --> 01:05:27.878
That's what you say now! ln six months,
you'll be looking for the back door!

01:05:27.968 --> 01:05:31.881
Oh, no, it's never gonna be over
between you and me! You get it?

01:05:31.968 --> 01:05:34.562
Go back to your mother, Linda!
I'm finished!

01:05:34.608 --> 01:05:37.441
Tell her I made
a mistake. Do it!

01:05:37.488 --> 01:05:40.480
You hear me? Tell her
you made a mistake! Don't touch me!

01:05:40.568 --> 01:05:45.323
I don't want you here!
I don't want you! Get out! Go!

01:05:45.408 --> 01:05:47.683
Leave me alone!

01:05:47.768 --> 01:05:49.724
Don't look at me
like that!

01:06:10.608 --> 01:06:12.997
Who is it? Who's there?

01:06:15.888 --> 01:06:19.164
Who is it?

01:06:19.208 --> 01:06:21.085
Who's there?

01:06:29.288 --> 01:06:32.997
Hi. I thought
l'd improve the view.

01:06:33.088 --> 01:06:36.000
Oh, look at
the big kung fu man.

01:06:36.048 --> 01:06:40.007
- First sign of trouble
and all he does is quit.
- Shut up! Shut up!

01:06:43.048 --> 01:06:46.802
See this notebook? Looks like the
ones we had in school, right?

01:06:46.888 --> 01:06:49.277
Wrong.
This is your future.

01:06:49.328 --> 01:06:53.003
- I don't have any more future.
- Sure, you do.

01:06:53.088 --> 01:06:56.763
You know, all I keep hearing
is the fight took too long.

01:06:56.808 --> 01:06:59.322
Too much tradition,
too much classical mess...

01:06:59.368 --> 01:07:01.928
too many fixed positions
in wing chun.

01:07:02.008 --> 01:07:04.920
You know everything
that's wrong, so fix it.

01:07:04.968 --> 01:07:07.402
Stop whining
and start fighting.

01:07:07.488 --> 01:07:09.524
Fight back
with your mind.

01:07:09.608 --> 01:07:14.318
- I can't write, I can't move!
- You talk, quitter. l'll write.

01:07:21.288 --> 01:07:25.600
- I'm waiting.
- lt would take forever.

01:07:25.648 --> 01:07:28.481
You goin' anywhere?

01:07:29.968 --> 01:07:33.597
I'm not.

01:07:33.648 --> 01:07:37.766
Oh, yeah, there's
just one more thing.

01:07:39.248 --> 01:07:42.081
I'm pregnant.

01:07:46.648 --> 01:07:51.358
The great mistake is to anticipate
the outcome of the engagement.

01:07:51.448 --> 01:07:53.279
You ought not
to be thinking...

01:07:53.368 --> 01:07:57.122
of whether it ends
in victory or defeat;

01:07:57.168 --> 01:08:00.240
but let nature
take its course...

01:08:00.328 --> 01:08:04.799
and your tools will strike
at the right moment.

01:08:04.848 --> 01:08:08.158
The consciousness of self
is the greatest hindrance...

01:08:08.208 --> 01:08:10.085
to the proper execution
of all--

01:08:10.128 --> 01:08:12.483
The knowledge and skill you have
achieved are meant to be forgotten.

01:08:12.568 --> 01:08:15.366
So you can float-- To obtain
enlightenment in martial art...

01:08:15.448 --> 01:08:17.484
means the extinction
of everything which--

01:08:17.568 --> 01:08:21.765
The way to transcend karma lies in
the proper use of the mind and the will.

01:08:21.808 --> 01:08:23.685
Jeet Kune Do
is not to hurt...

01:08:23.768 --> 01:08:26.885
but is one of the avenues through which
life opens its secrets to us.

01:08:26.968 --> 01:08:29.765
Relaxation
is essential...

01:08:29.848 --> 01:08:33.443
for faster and
more powerful punching.

01:08:33.528 --> 01:08:36.917
Let your lead punch
shoot up loosely and ea--

01:08:36.968 --> 01:08:39.277
An-And what? " Loosely and" what?

01:08:39.368 --> 01:08:42.644
- Loosely and easily!
-" Easily." Okay.

01:08:42.728 --> 01:08:45.925
Do not tighten up
or clench your fists...

01:08:45.968 --> 01:08:48.801
until the moment
of impact.

01:08:48.848 --> 01:08:50.725
- Aah! Aah.
- Okay, come on. Come on.

01:08:50.768 --> 01:08:54.044
All punches should end
with a snap several inches...

01:08:54.087 --> 01:08:56.807
- behind the target.
- Okay.

01:08:59.368 --> 01:09:01.198
Morning, ladies!

01:09:01.287 --> 01:09:04.724
- Congratulations, Mr. Lee.
- Thank you.

01:09:44.328 --> 01:09:46.398
Hey, kiddo.

01:09:46.448 --> 01:09:49.439
He's too young
to shave.

01:09:49.488 --> 01:09:53.447
They aren't shaving mirrors.
They're called pat kwa.

01:09:53.528 --> 01:09:56.679
Pat kwa?

01:09:56.768 --> 01:09:58.884
They're like gargoyles
on churches.

01:09:58.968 --> 01:10:02.722
You put them around
to ward off evil spirits.

01:10:06.448 --> 01:10:10.236
- I wanna call him Brandon.
- Brandon.

01:10:10.328 --> 01:10:12.319
That's good.

01:10:12.368 --> 01:10:14.677
Do you wanna hold him?

01:10:46.408 --> 01:10:49.241
- Oh, look at Daddy.
- Hey, big guy.

01:10:49.288 --> 01:10:52.644
Come on up here. Shh!

01:10:54.808 --> 01:10:58.084
- He's so tiny.
- Hi, baby.

01:10:58.128 --> 01:11:01.120
- Don't be afraid.
- He's so tiny.

01:11:02.568 --> 01:11:04.923
You're beautiful.

01:11:11.528 --> 01:11:14.884
- Bruce? Bruce,
come here! lt came!
- Yeah?

01:11:14.928 --> 01:11:17.158
Look! lt's here,
it's here, it's here!

01:11:17.248 --> 01:11:20.001
- Oh.
- Open it! Open it up quick!

01:11:25.288 --> 01:11:27.119
Whoa!

01:11:27.208 --> 01:11:29.768
lt's your book!
lt's your book.

01:11:29.848 --> 01:11:33.443
Look at that.

01:11:36.608 --> 01:11:39.406
Okay, hold on.
l'll get it.

01:11:49.528 --> 01:11:53.282
- Hi.
- Hi.

01:11:53.368 --> 01:11:57.361
- May I come in?
- Why?

01:11:57.448 --> 01:12:01.327
- I like your hair.
- Come on, Mom, I don't
wanna chitchat with you.

01:12:01.408 --> 01:12:04.639
- What are you doing here?
- I came to see you and--

01:12:04.688 --> 01:12:07.043
Did you come
to see me...

01:12:07.088 --> 01:12:10.763
or did you come to see
the yellow baby?

01:12:10.848 --> 01:12:14.557
- I think maybe I made a mistake.
- Brandon, it's Grandma!

01:12:14.608 --> 01:12:18.123
Grandma's come to see you!
Come on in, Grandma!

01:12:19.288 --> 01:12:21.961
There's someone
you ought to meet.

01:12:25.008 --> 01:12:26.885
Come on.

01:12:33.728 --> 01:12:35.719
How are you feeling,
Mr. Lee?

01:12:35.808 --> 01:12:39.562
- Oh, like half-man, half-car.
- Glad to hear it.

01:12:43.128 --> 01:12:46.962
Linda, your mom's got great legs.
Great legs!

01:12:54.528 --> 01:12:56.837
He looks--

01:12:59.048 --> 01:13:02.404
Well, he-- He looks
like both of you.

01:13:04.688 --> 01:13:06.963
May l?

01:13:28.008 --> 01:13:31.478
Oh, come on,
sweetheart.

01:13:31.528 --> 01:13:33.917
There you go.

01:13:33.968 --> 01:13:36.801
Hello. Yes.

01:13:36.848 --> 01:13:40.636
You're such
a handsome fella.

01:13:40.688 --> 01:13:42.679
He's gorgeous.

01:13:49.368 --> 01:13:51.802
He's so sweet.

01:13:51.848 --> 01:13:53.839
Oh, yes, you are.

01:13:58.728 --> 01:14:00.719
You did good,
sweetheart.

01:14:00.808 --> 01:14:04.164
You sure did good.
Gosh, yes.

01:14:04.208 --> 01:14:06.403
Look at you!

01:14:06.488 --> 01:14:11.198
Brandon, you're a strong one.
Only you could do this.

01:14:28.848 --> 01:14:32.238
The art of Jeet Kune Do
is simply to simplify.

01:14:32.328 --> 01:14:36.207
lt favors formlessness so that
it can assume all forms.

01:14:36.288 --> 01:14:39.360
Kung Fu, karate,
tae kwan do.

01:14:39.408 --> 01:14:41.922
All the classical styles
are attempts...

01:14:42.008 --> 01:14:44.283
to arrest
the flux of conflict.

01:14:44.328 --> 01:14:47.798
But in actual combat, the opponent
doesn't wait for formalities.

01:14:47.848 --> 01:14:50.885
He's not a robot, but a human
being, fluid and alive.

01:14:55.208 --> 01:14:58.245
For instance--
For instance!

01:14:58.328 --> 01:15:01.718
Like a sculptor who doesn't
keep adding clay to a statue...

01:15:01.768 --> 01:15:04.805
but strips away the inessentials
until the truth is revealed.

01:15:04.888 --> 01:15:08.164
I have developed a way of fighting
with no fixed positions...

01:15:08.248 --> 01:15:10.079
with no set movements.

01:15:18.448 --> 01:15:20.837
The fancy mess
of martial arts...

01:15:20.928 --> 01:15:23.362
solidifies
what was once fluid.

01:15:23.408 --> 01:15:27.367
lt is nothing but blind devotion
to the systematic uselessness...

01:15:27.408 --> 01:15:29.968
of routines
that lead nowhere.

01:15:30.048 --> 01:15:34.166
Calm down!

01:15:38.888 --> 01:15:41.925
Calm down! Calm down!

01:15:41.968 --> 01:15:44.323
- Tell him to prove it!
- Yeah!

01:15:44.408 --> 01:15:46.239
Tell him
to prove it!

01:15:46.328 --> 01:15:49.923
Mr. Lee is not here
for competition.

01:15:50.008 --> 01:15:51.964
Prove it! Prove it!

01:15:52.008 --> 01:15:54.317
- Prove it! Prove it!
- All right, calm down, calm down!

01:15:54.408 --> 01:15:57.718
- Keep it quiet! Mr. Lee--
- Prove it! Prove it!

01:15:57.768 --> 01:16:00.601
- Prove it! Prove it!
- Okay!

01:16:00.648 --> 01:16:02.639
Okay, l'll prove it.

01:16:04.648 --> 01:16:07.720
l'll need someone
to prove it on.

01:16:11.088 --> 01:16:13.363
l'll beat any man
in this room in 60 seconds!

01:16:13.448 --> 01:16:15.359
What?

01:16:18.728 --> 01:16:21.083
l'll fight him!

01:16:25.608 --> 01:16:29.078
I beat him before!

01:16:29.128 --> 01:16:32.438
I beat him again!

01:16:48.328 --> 01:16:51.365
What are you, crazy?
The doctor said no more fighting.

01:16:51.448 --> 01:16:53.916
They told me l'd
never walk again, too.

01:16:53.968 --> 01:16:57.119
When will you be happy?
When they're right?

01:16:57.168 --> 01:16:59.398
Bruce, I'm begging you.
lf you love me--

01:16:59.488 --> 01:17:02.161
- This isn't about you and me.
- Fine!

01:17:02.248 --> 01:17:05.718
But I'm not going through this again,
do you understand me?

01:17:05.768 --> 01:17:08.077
You get hurt,
you're on your own.

01:17:10.128 --> 01:17:12.961
Don't go
too far, hon!

01:17:13.048 --> 01:17:16.324
lt'll be over
in sixty seconds.

01:17:49.208 --> 01:17:52.280
This is
a challenge match...

01:17:52.328 --> 01:17:56.606
to prove Mr. Lee's theories
on Jeet Kune Do.

01:17:56.648 --> 01:17:59.321
Sixty seconds.

01:18:04.248 --> 01:18:06.682
Bow to the judges.

01:18:13.488 --> 01:18:16.321
Bow to each other.

01:18:20.088 --> 01:18:22.079
Begin!

01:20:21.328 --> 01:20:23.205
Jesus Christ!

01:21:00.808 --> 01:21:04.118
Bruce Lee! Bruce Lee!
Bruce Lee! Bruce Lee!

01:21:04.168 --> 01:21:08.161
Bruce Lee! Bruce Lee!
Bruce Lee! Bruce Lee!

01:21:08.248 --> 01:21:09.966
Bruce Lee! Bruce Lee!
Bruce Lee! Bruce Lee!

01:21:12.048 --> 01:21:15.961
- Yeah!
- Hey, Mr. Lee!

01:21:17.768 --> 01:21:20.965
Bill Krieger's the name. You looked
pretty great out there today.

01:21:21.048 --> 01:21:25.121
No, he didn't. He was too slow.
He took too long.

01:21:25.208 --> 01:21:27.563
You looked pretty fast to me.

01:21:27.648 --> 01:21:30.367
You think you can do some of
that stuff in front of a camera?

01:21:30.408 --> 01:21:34.640
- I'm a TV producer and--
- Right, and I'm Marvin Gaye.

01:21:34.728 --> 01:21:38.357
I'm casting my new series.
lt's called The Green Hornet...

01:21:38.408 --> 01:21:41.320
and I think
we could use you.

01:21:53.768 --> 01:21:56.646
So, d'you hear I bought
a house on the beach?

01:21:56.688 --> 01:21:58.565
Right in Malibu.
I'm tellin' ya...

01:21:58.608 --> 01:22:01.441
I got 120 yards of sand
as my front yard.

01:22:01.488 --> 01:22:05.242
Th-That's too tight. I can
sell the stunt. You don't have
to cut off the circulation.

01:22:05.288 --> 01:22:07.324
Cal, run him
through the scene.

01:22:07.368 --> 01:22:11.566
As soon as you get your cue light,
you come through that door.

01:22:11.648 --> 01:22:14.446
Then you work your way
down this catwalk here.

01:22:14.528 --> 01:22:17.247
Be real careful as
you negotiate this corner.

01:22:17.288 --> 01:22:20.280
I want you to get down these steps
as fast as you can.

01:22:20.328 --> 01:22:22.239
Not too fast.

01:22:22.328 --> 01:22:25.445
I don't want you to tumble. I don't
want to lose you on the first show.

01:22:25.488 --> 01:22:27.365
When you get
to this landing...

01:22:27.408 --> 01:22:30.047
do you think you could take
these five steps all at once?

01:22:30.088 --> 01:22:31.965
- l'll try.
- Atta boy.

01:22:32.008 --> 01:22:34.602
First positions, everybody!

01:22:34.688 --> 01:22:37.043
Hey, can you tell
it's me?

01:22:38.568 --> 01:22:41.401
I just talked to the network.
They love the dailies. They love 'em.

01:22:41.448 --> 01:22:44.167
- Don't they always?
- Yeah. Listen, there's, uh--

01:22:44.248 --> 01:22:48.241
- There's one small problem.
- Lemme call you back.

01:22:48.328 --> 01:22:52.321
- Yeah, what is it?
- Uh, it's this guy Lee.

01:22:52.368 --> 01:22:55.360
You know, he's
awfully... Oriental.

01:22:55.408 --> 01:22:57.558
- He's supposed to be Oriental.
- Yeah.

01:22:57.608 --> 01:22:59.997
- He's playing an Oriental.
- I know, I know. What?

01:23:00.048 --> 01:23:02.642
- Kato is Oriental.
- I know, I know.

01:23:02.728 --> 01:23:05.720
Uh, can you just make sure
he keeps the mask on?

01:23:05.768 --> 01:23:09.283
Roll sound!
Roll camera!

01:23:09.368 --> 01:23:12.804
And mark it!

01:23:14.728 --> 01:23:17.686
- Action!
- All right, Green Hornet...

01:23:17.768 --> 01:23:19.838
where's
the secret formula?

01:23:19.928 --> 01:23:25.048
- Where it belongs.
- Okay, have it your way.

01:23:37.368 --> 01:23:39.165
Kato!

01:23:48.008 --> 01:23:50.238
Good work, Kato!

01:23:50.328 --> 01:23:53.286
Good work, Kato!

01:23:53.368 --> 01:23:55.643
Ow! Ow!

01:23:57.128 --> 01:23:59.596
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

01:24:03.768 --> 01:24:06.566
- Good work, Kato.
- Thanks, boss.

01:24:09.928 --> 01:24:14.399
Huh? Ah, cut, cut, cut!

01:24:14.448 --> 01:24:16.643
That's a print.

01:24:16.688 --> 01:24:19.646
Thought that'd be
a little more exciting.

01:24:22.608 --> 01:24:25.361
lf he came from Hong Kong,
he'd end up in San Francisco.

01:24:25.448 --> 01:24:28.246
- I don't wanna do the urban thing.
- We helped with the railroads.

01:24:28.328 --> 01:24:31.206
- How about the Wild West?
- Okay, great. The Wild West.

01:24:31.288 --> 01:24:33.438
- Okay.
- Chinese immigrant wanders the land.

01:24:33.528 --> 01:24:36.759
- He's a good guy, a hero.
- Of course, he's a hero.
He's the star of the show.

01:24:36.808 --> 01:24:38.685
He wanders the land
solving problems.

01:24:38.728 --> 01:24:41.925
- Every week he solves a problem.
- With no gun. Just his hands.

01:24:42.008 --> 01:24:43.919
That's good.
That's great. No gun.

01:24:44.008 --> 01:24:47.398
- He's looking for something.
- His father. He lost his father
who came ahead of him.

01:24:47.488 --> 01:24:50.844
No, no, not the father. The father
thing has been done to death.

01:24:50.888 --> 01:24:52.765
- He's searching for his brother.
- Good.

01:24:52.808 --> 01:24:54.685
- Searching for his brother.
- He never finds him.

01:24:54.728 --> 01:24:58.403
- Not until the fifth year.
- He wanders the land,
searching for his brother...

01:24:58.488 --> 01:25:02.117
- solving problems with no gun.
- And he has something
no one else has ever seen.

01:25:02.208 --> 01:25:04.768
- Kung Fu! Starring Bruce Lee.
- Kung Fu! Uh-huh.

01:25:04.808 --> 01:25:07.845
He remembers what he was taught
in the old country by his teacher...

01:25:07.928 --> 01:25:09.759
and teaches people
his culture.

01:25:09.848 --> 01:25:12.646
After he's kicked the shit
out of everybody. Fantastic!

01:25:12.728 --> 01:25:15.959
- We've got action, culture!
lt's a western!
- But it's an Eastern.

01:25:16.008 --> 01:25:18.238
lt's an Eastern.
Right. lt's an Eastern.

01:25:18.288 --> 01:25:20.756
They're gonna love it.
This thing's gonna run forever!

01:25:20.808 --> 01:25:22.685
- Kung Fu!
- Kung Fu!

01:25:23.928 --> 01:25:25.407
Easy, easy.

01:25:35.208 --> 01:25:37.199
Wow.

01:25:37.288 --> 01:25:40.564
- You steal Steve McQueen's car?
- He stole mine.

01:25:40.648 --> 01:25:43.037
- Come on, get in. We're late.
- Okay.

01:25:43.128 --> 01:25:45.403
What? Linda. Hey.

01:25:45.448 --> 01:25:48.645
-l--
-You do the clutch, l'll work the stick.

01:26:24.488 --> 01:26:26.399
Bruce! Linda!

01:26:26.448 --> 01:26:30.077
- So glad you guys could make it.
Go on in. We'll be right down.
- Okay.

01:26:30.128 --> 01:26:32.323
This way, please.

01:26:50.728 --> 01:26:54.118
Excuse me, Mr. Krieger,
there's a phone call.

01:26:54.208 --> 01:26:56.164
Excuse me.

01:26:58.728 --> 01:27:01.561
Did I ever tell you I was
the cha-cha champion of Hong Kong?

01:27:01.608 --> 01:27:04.327
About 15,000 times.

01:27:04.368 --> 01:27:08.122
- Did I ever tell you I was pregnant?
- Once.

01:27:08.168 --> 01:27:11.524
Make that twice.

01:27:16.528 --> 01:27:19.326
Hold it, everybody!
Hold it!

01:27:19.488 --> 01:27:23.447
Hold it!

01:27:23.488 --> 01:27:26.321
I know the timing
is lousy, but, uh...

01:27:26.368 --> 01:27:29.201
I wanted you to hear it
first from me personally.

01:27:29.248 --> 01:27:31.682
The show's been cancelled.

01:27:31.768 --> 01:27:33.599
- What?
- Oh, no.

01:27:33.688 --> 01:27:36.805
I know it's a bummer, but we'll
finish out the last episodes...

01:27:36.888 --> 01:27:39.800
and, uh, that'll be that.

01:27:39.888 --> 01:27:42.527
I'm sorry.

01:27:42.608 --> 01:27:45.486
Enjoy the rest of the party.

01:27:47.608 --> 01:27:51.647
Bill and I will just roll
into Kung Fu!

01:27:51.688 --> 01:27:53.963
1, 2, cha-cha-cha.

01:27:54.048 --> 01:27:56.846
1, 2, cha-cha-cha.
1 and 2 and 3 and 4...

01:27:56.928 --> 01:28:00.204
and 1 and 2 and 3 and 4.
1, 2, cha-cha-cha.

01:28:00.288 --> 01:28:03.325
Uh-huh. Uh-huh.

01:28:03.408 --> 01:28:07.640
So what are they saying at
the network about Kung Fu?

01:28:07.728 --> 01:28:10.242
Right.

01:28:10.328 --> 01:28:12.523
And when do you think
they'll know?

01:28:12.608 --> 01:28:16.521
Oh, Bill, Bill, Bill.
What about dinner?

01:28:16.608 --> 01:28:18.678
Call me back.

01:28:29.088 --> 01:28:32.603
They still haven't made
any decisions on the show.

01:28:32.688 --> 01:28:35.646
- Still looks good.
- Good.

01:28:35.688 --> 01:28:37.963
Don't worry.

01:28:38.048 --> 01:28:40.608
Who else are they gonna get,
Mickey Rooney?

01:28:40.688 --> 01:28:42.679
I'm not worried.

01:28:44.288 --> 01:28:46.597
I'm not worried.

01:29:30.568 --> 01:29:32.445
Hello?

01:29:34.688 --> 01:29:37.521
- Really?
- As quickly as you can...

01:29:37.568 --> 01:29:39.957
snatch the pebble
from my hand.

01:29:40.248 --> 01:29:41.886
All right.

01:29:44.448 --> 01:29:47.838
- Okay.
- When you can take
the pebble from my hand...

01:29:47.928 --> 01:29:50.158
it will be time
for you to leave.

01:29:51.688 --> 01:29:54.077
What's wrong, honey?

01:29:56.768 --> 01:29:59.566
My father's dead.

01:31:08.328 --> 01:31:11.161
- lt comes, it goes.
- ln your dream?

01:31:11.208 --> 01:31:14.757
No, I'm always awake.
lt's not a dream, sifu.

01:31:14.848 --> 01:31:18.284
When your father first brought
you here, he told me everything.

01:31:18.368 --> 01:31:20.518
He wanted you to learn
wing chun...

01:31:20.608 --> 01:31:23.168
to protect yourself
against man...

01:31:23.208 --> 01:31:25.722
- and other forces.
- I thought that was all superstition.

01:31:25.768 --> 01:31:31.001
Superstition is a name the ignorant
give to their ignorance.

01:31:31.048 --> 01:31:34.040
You were special then,
and you're special now.

01:31:34.088 --> 01:31:36.761
That's why the demon
wants you.

01:31:39.008 --> 01:31:42.637
We have spent a lot of time together,
preparing you for this.

01:31:47.128 --> 01:31:49.323
Good. Good.

01:31:49.408 --> 01:31:51.717
Very good.

01:31:54.088 --> 01:31:57.239
What if I won't fight him?

01:31:57.288 --> 01:31:59.165
You have no choice.

01:31:59.208 --> 01:32:03.759
-You're fighting for more than yourself.
-What are you saying, sifu?

01:32:03.808 --> 01:32:07.801
As I told you, this demon
is your inner fear.

01:32:07.848 --> 01:32:11.124
lt doesn't matter
how many men you defeat.

01:32:11.168 --> 01:32:13.557
lf you don't conquer
your own fears...

01:32:13.608 --> 01:32:16.168
you will pass your demons
on to your children...

01:32:16.248 --> 01:32:19.399
as your father passed his
on to you.

01:32:21.728 --> 01:32:23.605
No.

01:32:23.648 --> 01:32:25.525
You will fight him.

01:32:30.448 --> 01:32:33.246
When you are
at your absolute peak...

01:32:33.288 --> 01:32:35.483
he will come to you.

01:32:35.528 --> 01:32:38.838
When the monsoon blow,
be prepared.

01:33:45.728 --> 01:33:48.959
Mr. Lee! Mr. Lee!

01:33:49.048 --> 01:33:51.687
l've been chasing you
all over Hong Kong.

01:33:51.768 --> 01:33:53.804
You should buy a car.

01:33:53.888 --> 01:33:57.563
- Just a joke.
- I'm Philip Tan.

01:33:57.648 --> 01:34:00.208
I'm a producer. I want to
make a picture with you.

01:34:00.288 --> 01:34:03.280
- Talk is cheap. Pictures are expensive.
- I'm on the level.

01:34:03.328 --> 01:34:05.398
You're Kato,
and over here...

01:34:05.488 --> 01:34:08.446
Kato has a small
but loyal following.

01:34:08.528 --> 01:34:10.405
Something we can build on.

01:34:10.488 --> 01:34:13.719
They don't call your show The Green
Hornet. lt's called The Kato Show.

01:34:13.808 --> 01:34:16.766
Did you know that?
Well, it's true.

01:34:16.808 --> 01:34:20.084
When I hear Kato is in town,
I consider it a good omen.

01:34:20.128 --> 01:34:23.245
- l've got to get back to my family.
- Leave tomorrow. Give us time.

01:34:23.328 --> 01:34:26.604
-l've been away for so long.
-l'll buy you a new ticket, first class.

01:34:26.688 --> 01:34:29.521
l'll take care of everything.
One more day, please.

01:34:29.568 --> 01:34:32.128
You can't lose.

01:34:32.168 --> 01:34:34.045
What's the movie?

01:34:57.888 --> 01:35:00.277
Action! Action!

01:35:00.368 --> 01:35:02.836
Action!

01:35:25.608 --> 01:35:27.564
My brother can't talk right.

01:35:27.648 --> 01:35:29.479
He can't walk right.

01:35:29.568 --> 01:35:31.798
You have dishonored
my family.

01:35:31.848 --> 01:35:33.725
- I have sworn to kill you.
- Swearing is easy.

01:35:37.248 --> 01:35:41.526
I read your book.
I know all your tricks.

01:35:41.568 --> 01:35:44.128
Let's see how well you've
learned your lesson.

01:39:37.928 --> 01:39:42.479
lt's so hot in here, I like
to put my dolly in the refrigerator.

01:39:42.528 --> 01:39:44.519
Yeah, that was fun!

01:39:44.608 --> 01:39:46.644
- We missed you!
- I missed you too!

01:39:46.688 --> 01:39:48.644
- I missed you.
- I missed you!

01:40:46.968 --> 01:40:48.924
Hurry up! Over there!

01:40:51.968 --> 01:40:54.562
Listen, Cheng, give up.

01:40:56.968 --> 01:40:59.243
Cheng!

01:40:59.328 --> 01:41:01.159
Ohh!

01:41:04.528 --> 01:41:06.359
lt's okay, Mei.

01:41:27.648 --> 01:41:30.321
Let's get out of here
before they lynch us.

01:42:06.608 --> 01:42:09.486
Yeah! Hey!

01:42:09.568 --> 01:42:12.765
Bruce!

01:42:47.728 --> 01:42:50.367
Bruce!

01:42:50.408 --> 01:42:52.524
Linda!

01:42:52.608 --> 01:42:54.439
Bruce!

01:42:56.448 --> 01:42:59.008
Bruce!

01:44:14.528 --> 01:44:16.439
Daddy's taking me
to the circus!

01:44:16.488 --> 01:44:18.956
Oh, my.

01:44:19.008 --> 01:44:22.045
- Okay, Brandon, go change.
Don't keep Daddy waiting.
- Okay!

01:44:31.208 --> 01:44:33.676
Okay, back! Back!
Number two. Number two.

01:44:37.248 --> 01:44:39.478
lt's okay.

01:44:39.528 --> 01:44:41.962
Come on, big boy.

01:44:42.048 --> 01:44:44.004
Come on.

01:44:44.088 --> 01:44:48.604
Your bed is so much more cozy.
Come on.

01:44:48.688 --> 01:44:51.122
We'll go up to your bed with
the covers and everything.

01:45:13.568 --> 01:45:17.766
Somewhere there's gotta be
a series in all this.

01:45:21.768 --> 01:45:25.647
Three minutes.
lt's like doing 200 pushups.

01:45:29.328 --> 01:45:31.205
- Wanna try?
- Uh, no thanks.

01:45:31.288 --> 01:45:34.883
- You might turn it up
and try to electrocute me.
- The thought crossed my mind.

01:45:34.968 --> 01:45:37.562
Justifiable homicide,
some might say.

01:45:37.608 --> 01:45:40.520
What do you want, Bill?

01:45:40.608 --> 01:45:44.840
- You didn't come here
to discuss old times.
- I came to discuss new times.

01:45:44.928 --> 01:45:48.921
There's somebody I want you to meet.
His name is Freddie Weintraub.

01:45:49.008 --> 01:45:50.839
We've got a project for you.

01:45:50.928 --> 01:45:53.601
What's the matter,
David Carradine turn you down?

01:45:53.688 --> 01:45:57.283
No, Fred's got a script.
lt's called Enter The Dragon.

01:45:57.368 --> 01:46:00.166
We're gonna shoot it here,
but it's your ticket back to America.

01:46:00.248 --> 01:46:03.001
lt's a feature.

01:46:03.048 --> 01:46:05.039
A Hollywood feature.

01:46:05.088 --> 01:46:08.000
With all the trimmings.
Hmm?

01:46:08.088 --> 01:46:10.966
Hey!

01:46:41.128 --> 01:46:43.005
Ohh.

01:46:43.048 --> 01:46:45.118
lt's okay.

01:46:45.208 --> 01:46:47.039
I'm awake.

01:46:48.328 --> 01:46:50.603
I was working
on Game Of Death.

01:46:50.688 --> 01:46:52.519
Lost track of time.

01:46:54.128 --> 01:46:57.086
The kids okay?

01:46:57.168 --> 01:47:01.081
Don't you ever get tired
of asking that question?

01:47:01.128 --> 01:47:03.722
Linda, we've been
through this before.

01:47:03.808 --> 01:47:06.561
I don't have a choice.

01:47:06.648 --> 01:47:09.208
You might not...

01:47:09.248 --> 01:47:11.443
but I do.

01:47:11.488 --> 01:47:14.798
I'm taking the kids
and going home for a while.

01:47:14.848 --> 01:47:19.205
- Home's here for now.
- No. Here is where we watch you work.

01:47:19.288 --> 01:47:23.201
- What do you want me to do?
- I want you to come with us.

01:47:23.288 --> 01:47:26.325
Forget it.

01:47:26.368 --> 01:47:29.201
I worked in America for ten years
and what did it get me?

01:47:29.248 --> 01:47:33.036
- lt got me nothing.
- lt got you me.

01:47:33.088 --> 01:47:35.727
Oh, man.

01:47:35.808 --> 01:47:38.561
They got such
a good line of bullshit.

01:47:38.648 --> 01:47:41.446
"Come and get it!"
"America, the mountain of gold!"

01:47:41.528 --> 01:47:43.962
"lt's for everybody!"
Yeah, it's for everybody white!

01:47:44.008 --> 01:47:47.637
But they don't tell you that!
You gotta read the small print!

01:47:47.688 --> 01:47:49.565
lf you can read.

01:47:50.888 --> 01:47:53.083
I am not America.

01:47:53.168 --> 01:47:56.683
Your kids are not America.
Don't push us away.

01:47:59.968 --> 01:48:02.721
We're going.

01:48:02.808 --> 01:48:05.117
I want you
to come with us.

01:48:08.368 --> 01:48:11.519
I want the kids
to have a father again.

01:48:11.608 --> 01:48:13.724
Don't lay any
guilt trips on me!

01:48:13.768 --> 01:48:17.556
- I'm not taking any guilt trips!
- This place is eating us up!

01:48:17.648 --> 01:48:21.357
- Can't you see that, Bruce?
- This place has given us a life!

01:48:21.408 --> 01:48:23.842
I'm somebody here!
I'm special!

01:48:23.928 --> 01:48:25.998
Back there,
I'm just another gook!

01:48:26.048 --> 01:48:30.007
Just another wetback, Charlie Chan,
slopehead, coolie dishwasher...

01:48:30.048 --> 01:48:32.164
in a stinking Chinkie
restaurant!

01:48:32.248 --> 01:48:33.886
Mom!

01:48:33.928 --> 01:48:35.964
Wash your shirt, Mister White Man?

01:48:36.008 --> 01:48:38.647
Please?
No tickee, no shirtee!

01:48:38.688 --> 01:48:42.237
- Order one from column " A"
and one from column " B."
- Mommy!

01:48:42.328 --> 01:48:44.159
Me happy to build
the railroads...

01:48:44.248 --> 01:48:46.716
to dig the mines for you,
Mister White Man!

01:48:48.728 --> 01:48:51.959
- Mommy, I'm scared! What's happening?
- ls that who I am?

01:48:52.008 --> 01:48:54.966
ls it? Tell me!
Tell me that's who I am!

01:48:55.008 --> 01:48:58.318
I don't know who the hell
you are anymore!

01:48:59.968 --> 01:49:02.687
- Do you?
- Mommy, what's happening?

01:49:21.888 --> 01:49:25.244
Weintraub's script is called Enter
The Dragon. I read it. lt's really good.

01:49:25.328 --> 01:49:28.798
- I thought we were partners.
I made you my partner!
- We are partners!

01:49:28.888 --> 01:49:30.719
I told him without you,
no deal.

01:49:30.808 --> 01:49:32.958
"A Co-production ln Association
With Philip Tan" ?

01:49:33.048 --> 01:49:35.516
- That's an insult!
- You could get more.

01:49:35.608 --> 01:49:38.680
- lt's not about getting more.
We don't need them!
- Yes, we do.

01:49:38.728 --> 01:49:41.959
lt's Warner Brothers,
big budget, in English, with
international distribution!

01:49:42.048 --> 01:49:45.085
Don't sell me, Bruce!
Don't sell a salesman!

01:49:52.488 --> 01:49:55.048
Do you have an aspirin?

01:50:11.888 --> 01:50:15.483
I don't know, man. I don't know
how much longer I can keep this up.

01:50:19.568 --> 01:50:22.560
You want it so bad,
don't you?

01:50:22.648 --> 01:50:24.878
You want their love so bad.

01:50:24.928 --> 01:50:26.805
Our love's
not good enough for you.

01:50:26.848 --> 01:50:30.557
When I was a kid,
I had all these crazy ideas.

01:50:32.248 --> 01:50:36.639
I wanted to show the world the beauty
of our culture, to give them a hero.

01:50:36.728 --> 01:50:39.481
- But a Chinese hero.
- You have.

01:50:39.528 --> 01:50:41.405
Don't you see that?

01:50:44.448 --> 01:50:46.564
I want something else now.

01:50:48.608 --> 01:50:51.839
I want to stop breaking
my wife's heart.

01:50:51.928 --> 01:50:55.204
I want to play with my children
without having to look at the clock.

01:50:58.328 --> 01:51:00.284
They're American.

01:51:01.768 --> 01:51:04.601
I need to get back to America
or l'll lose them.

01:51:09.688 --> 01:51:12.441
lf I lose them,
nothing means anything.

01:53:36.928 --> 01:53:38.725
Look!

01:53:41.808 --> 01:53:43.844
No.

01:53:43.928 --> 01:53:48.285
No!

01:53:48.328 --> 01:53:51.684
Nooo!

01:53:51.768 --> 01:53:54.236
Nooooooo!

01:53:56.768 --> 01:53:58.998
Daddy! Dad!

01:53:59.088 --> 01:54:04.481
- Dad, come home! Dad!
- Brandon, run!

01:54:04.568 --> 01:54:08.447
- Run, Brandon! Run, Brandon! Go!
- Dad! Come on, Dad!

01:54:08.488 --> 01:54:11.366
Brandon, run!

01:54:11.448 --> 01:54:14.008
- Aaah!
- Dad?

01:54:14.048 --> 01:54:18.678
Dad! Dad, he's coming! Dad!

01:54:20.168 --> 01:54:24.081
Come on, Dad!
Dad, he's coming!

01:54:29.008 --> 01:54:31.158
Dad!

01:54:37.248 --> 01:54:39.637
lt's okay, Brandon!
lt's okay!

01:54:42.568 --> 01:54:45.287
Dad!

01:54:46.088 --> 01:54:48.886
Now, Brandon, now!
Now! Run!

01:55:35.008 --> 01:55:38.080
Kind of lost you there
for a minute, bud. You okay?

01:55:43.128 --> 01:55:45.005
Bruce? You all right?

01:55:45.048 --> 01:55:46.959
You all right?

01:56:01.688 --> 01:56:03.679
Dad! What are you
doing here?

01:56:03.728 --> 01:56:06.879
I live here.

01:56:06.928 --> 01:56:09.488
- Hey, can I play with you guys?
- Sure.

01:56:09.528 --> 01:56:12.406
Daddy, we had a typhoon.

01:56:13.488 --> 01:56:15.319
I know.

01:56:16.728 --> 01:56:19.288
But it's over now.

01:56:19.368 --> 01:56:23.759
Okay, Dad, l'll be
the engineer, you be the switcher.

01:56:23.848 --> 01:56:26.123
Hey, that sounds great.

01:56:31.368 --> 01:56:33.962
Last shot.

01:56:34.008 --> 01:56:36.568
Make it great.

01:56:54.208 --> 01:56:57.006
- Linda, I forgot something.
- What?

01:56:58.328 --> 01:57:01.161
I forgot to tell you
I love you.

01:57:03.808 --> 01:57:06.880
You know, I don't think you've
ever said that to me before.

01:57:06.928 --> 01:57:09.761
Yeah, but I meant it
every day.

01:57:43.528 --> 01:57:46.326
Three weeks before
the opening of Enter the Dragon...

01:57:46.408 --> 01:57:48.638
the film that brought him
international fame...

01:57:48.688 --> 01:57:51.680
Bruce fell into
a mysterious coma and died.

01:57:51.728 --> 01:57:53.639
He was 32.

01:57:53.728 --> 01:57:57.482
Over 25,000 people attended
his funeral in Hong Kong...

01:57:57.568 --> 01:58:01.607
but I buried him back home
in America to be close to us.

01:58:01.648 --> 01:58:05.482
All these years later, people still
wonder about the way he died.

01:58:05.568 --> 01:58:08.366
I prefer to remember
the way he lived.

